The paper focuses on data augmentation techniques for convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image classification. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the regularization effects of data augmentation compared to other techniques, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper analyzes the adaptability of networks trained with different amounts of data and architectures, which could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of data augmentation on natural language processing tasks, which could be relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
